718849f-a.text:
Church Street, north from and including Liberty Street, as seen from No. 74 Trinity Place, between Thames and Rector Streets. Also shown is the Sixth Ave. Elevated Line running north to Murray Street, where it makes a sharp bend westward. It continues on the latter street to West
Broadway where it resumes its northward course again.
August 20, 1929.
P. L. Sperr.
718849f-a.folder: Church Street & Liberty Street, Manhattan, NY

721130f-a.text:
Liberty Strect, nortn side, between Greenwich and
Vashington Streets, showing a 9 foot alley between No's 129 and 131 which according to the City Record appears to be ownerless. Its is 72 feet deep and of irregular width, leading to the rear of buildings that face on tne west side of Greenwich Street. At the nortnern extremity is the side of tne building in which John Thomas Smith lived and recently cied in; No. 154 Greenwich Street.
August 1938
George o. Chinn
